        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Violet",
        "type": "Person",
        "description": "A chimpanzee in Group 2 who made 38 observations but did not acquire the skill.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:18:16.585Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Vis",
        "type": "Person",
        "description": "A chimpanzee in Group 2 who made 25 observations but did not acquire the skill.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:18:16.719Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Zsabu",
        "type": "Person",
        "description": "A chimpanzee in Group 2 who made 9 observations but did not acquire the skill.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:18:16.851Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Social Transmission",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The process by which knowledge or skills are passed from one individual to another, identified in the study as the primary mechanism for skill acquisition in chimpanzees.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:18:55.143Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Asocial Learning",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Learning acquired independently without social input, used as a baseline rate in the study to contrast with social transmission effects.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:18:55.278Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Task Solution Observation",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The act of witnessing another individual successfully solve the puzzle box task, identified as the strongest predictor of social transmission rate.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:02.124Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Individual Solving Observation",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The act of witnessing another individual attempting or solving the task, a secondary predictor of social transmission rate compared to observing successful solutions.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:02.254Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Two-Stage Learning Process",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A model of skill acquisition breaking down learning into first interacting with the apparatus and second actually solving it, with different social influences on each stage.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:02.389Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Apparatus Interaction",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The initial stage of the two-stage learning process where chimpanzees begin to physically engage with the puzzle box, influenced by the number of successes observed.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:02.513Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Task Solving",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The second stage of the two-stage learning process where chimpanzees successfully operate the mechanism to receive a reward, showing a stronger social learning effect than initial interaction.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:02.641Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Sex",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A demographic variable tested in the study, found to have no significant influence on the rate of social or asocial learning.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:02.773Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Social Rank",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A hierarchical status variable tested in the study, found to have no significant influence on the rate of social or asocial learning.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:02.906Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Age",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A demographic variable tested in the study, found to have no significant influence on the rate of social or asocial learning.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:03.039Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Asocial Learning Model Support",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The statistical support level for the hypothesis of purely asocial learning in the study, found to be very low at 0.6%, providing strong evidence against it as the primary mechanism.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:53.808Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Social Effect Estimate",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The model-averaged estimate of the social transmission parameter (s), calculated at 0.023 with a 95% confidence interval of 0.009–0.58, indicating a significant positive social influence on learning.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:57.660Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Group Network Hypothesis",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The hypothesis that social transmission follows the pattern of observations within each specific group, which received 65.3 times more support than alternative models.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:57.786Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Supplementary Information Section 4g",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A specific section in the study's supplementary materials containing detailed statistical models and tables (Tables 3 and 4) regarding the network-based diffusion analysis results.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:57.924Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Supplementary Tables 3 and 4",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Data tables within the supplementary information that provide detailed statistical results supporting the conclusions about social transmission rates and model comparisons.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:58.060Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Absolute Observation Network",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The specific social network model used for estimating social effects, which received the most statistical support and was used as the basis for conditional estimates of the social transmission parameter.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:58.187Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Dynamic Observation Network",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "An alternative social network model considered in the analysis, where the social parameter estimates were made conditional on the absolute observation network due to lower support.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:58.314Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Akaike Weight",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A statistical metric used to compare the relative likelihood of different models, with the least supported model in this study having a weight of 5 × 10^-7.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:58.446Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "95% Confidence Interval Lower Limit",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The lower bound of the confidence interval for the social transmission parameter, which was greater than 0 in all but the least supported model, confirming the presence of social transmission.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:19:58.579Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Proficient Conspecific Model",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A chimpanzee independently trained to function as a demonstrator for their group members during the social learning phase, seeding the group with skilled behavior.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:20:46.911Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Response Facilitation",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A mechanism where an individual uses a familiar action in a novel context, inferred by some authors as the likely process in certain chimpanzee learning scenarios rather than true know-how copying.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:20:47.043Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Skill Adopters",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The subset of 14 naive chimpanzees who successfully learned the puzzle box skill from demonstrators within two months, having observed successful task manipulations at least nine times.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:20:47.173Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Learning Rate Increase",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The observed acceleration in skill acquisition, where for every observation, the chimpanzee's learning rate increased by at least 0.461 times the asocial baseline rate.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:20:47.296Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Koops",
        "type": "Person",
        "description": "Researcher who conducted a study on wild chimpanzees and nut-cracking techniques, providing evidence against the idea that complex skills are solely individually reinvented.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:22:19.884Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Uncracked Nuts",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A necessary elemental component for nut-cracking, provided to wild chimpanzees in Koops' study, which alone did not facilitate skill acquisition.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:22:25.839Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Cracked Nuts",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A necessary elemental component for nut-cracking, provided to wild chimpanzees in Koops' study, which alone did not facilitate skill acquisition.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:22:25.962Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Cracking Tools",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A necessary elemental component for nut-cracking, provided to wild chimpanzees in Koops' study, which alone did not facilitate skill acquisition.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:22:29.718Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Opaque Sequence of Behaviours",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A complex, non-intuitive series of actions required to solve the puzzle box task, making independent invention unlikely without social information.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:22:29.852Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Collective Action",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A cornerstone of Cumulative Cultural Evolution in humans, involving the accumulation of improvements by multiple individuals, which the study argues is distinct from the observed chimpanzee behavior.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:22:29.979Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Parsimony",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The scientific principle often cited by ZLS proponents to argue that wild chimpanzee cultures are collections of individual re-innovations rather than socially transmitted know-how.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:22:30.106Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Socially Learned Tradition",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A behavioral pattern transmitted through social learning across generations, allowing chimpanzees to achieve mastery beyond their Zone of Latent Solutions.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:23:51.924Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Nut Cracking Motivation",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A critique factor suggesting that naive chimpanzees in previous studies may have lacked the motivation to crack or eat distributed nuts, confounding results on individual innovation capacity.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:23:52.738Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Temporal Order Requirement",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The necessity for actions in the puzzle box task to be executed in a specific sequence, which substantially complicates the task and makes independent invention unlikely.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:23:56.600Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Genetic Predispositions",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Innate biological tendencies that may partially predispose chimpanzees to certain components of a task, distinct from the learned sequence of behaviors.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:23:56.738Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Space of Know-how",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The theoretical range of behaviors chimpanzees can individually invent or imagine without social input, which the studied skill fell outside of.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:23:56.873Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Conducive Ecological Environment",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The specific setting of the study, characterized by a group setting allowing natural social dynamics and a forested home-range territory, contrasting with constrained zoo settings typical in other Cumulative Cultural Evolution studies.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:25:07.052Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Forested Home-range Territory",
        "type": "Location",
        "description": "The naturalistic environment where the chimpanzees were tested, providing an ecologically valid context for observing social learning, distinct from artificial laboratory or zoo environments.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:25:07.177Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Zoo Settings",
        "type": "Location",
        "description": "Constrained environments typically used in studies on Cumulative Cultural Evolution in chimpanzees, cited here as a contrast to the more naturalistic forested home-range territory used in this study.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:25:07.303Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Dead End of Individual Attempts",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The state of inability to solve the task independently experienced by chimpanzees during the baseline phase, which was overcome only after social information was introduced via a trained model.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:25:07.427Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Cue Longevity",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A moderating potential in social transmission studies, referring to how long social cues or information remain available or influential for learners, cited in the context of follow-up studies on Cumulative Cultural Evolution.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:10.076Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Contingent Reiterations",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A mechanism in social transmission involving repeated, context-dependent actions that facilitate the transfer of complex skills, cited as a factor alongside social transmission in the acquisition of cultural behaviors.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:10.201Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Barbary Macaques",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A primate species studied in recent research involving a novel foraging task (pushing a rotating door), providing comparative evidence for social learning mechanisms distinct from the chimpanzee puzzle box study.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:10.327Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Rotating Door Task",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A novel foraging task presented to Barbary macaques, requiring the pushing of a rotating door, used to study social learning and skill acquisition in non-human primates.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:10.456Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Social Norms",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Cultural manifestations that may require high-fidelity know-how copying for transmission, contrasting with cultural artefacts which might suffice with lower-fidelity mechanisms.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:14.845Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Cultural Artefacts",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Cultural manifestations such as tool usage that may not strictly require high-fidelity know-how copying, as mechanisms yielding less-high-fidelity transmission may suffice for their acquisition.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:14.970Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Task-naive State",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The initial condition of chimpanzees before exposure to the puzzle box, characterized by a lack of knowledge or skill regarding the apparatus, which transitions to engagement through social learning.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:15.102Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Apparatus Engagement",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The intermediate phase in skill acquisition where chimpanzees begin interacting with the puzzle box, facilitated by social learning and attraction to the actions of others.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:15.235Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Humans",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Described as an intrinsically cultural species that absorbs cultural information like sponges, often adopting behaviors culturally rather than through individual innovation even when capable of doing so.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:45.468Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Within-ZLS Transmission",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The transmission of behaviors that fall within an individual's Zone of Latent Solutions (i.e., they could innovate them individually) but are instead acquired or reinforced through social learning, providing fitness benefits.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:45.607Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Fitness Benefits",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Advantages gained from social transmission of innovations, including instrumental benefits (e.g., efficiency, resource access) and social benefits, which reduce the latency of acquiring useful behaviors compared to individual re-innovation.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:45.729Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Instrumental Benefits",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Practical advantages derived from social learning, such as faster access to resources or reduced effort, distinct from social benefits.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:45.856Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Social Benefits",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Advantages derived from social learning related to group cohesion, status, or interaction, distinct from instrumental benefits.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:45.982Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Non-human Animal Species",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Animal groups, including chimpanzees, that possess within-ZLS culture, demonstrating that social transmission of individually innovatable behaviors is not unique to humans.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:46.115Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Chimpanzee Caretakers",
        "type": "Person",
        "description": "Staff members who regularly checked the apparatus functionality and monitored for successful ball insertions to ensure the baseline condition (no independent success) remained valid.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:52.020Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "GoPro Camera",
        "type": "Tool",
        "description": "Motion-sensitive camera equipment attached to the puzzle box apparatus to record all interactions and events surrounding the device.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:26:52.142Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Bonobos",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A primate species cited alongside chimpanzees and orangutans as having a steadily growing list of documented cultural traditions, indicating the presence of within-ZLS culture.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:27:27.652Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Orangutans",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A primate species cited alongside chimpanzees and bonobos as having a steadily growing list of documented cultural traditions, supporting the argument for non-human animal culture.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:27:27.794Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Extended Baseline Period",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "An eight-month phase following the initial three-month baseline where the puzzle box apparatus remained in the chimpanzees' enclosures and was irregularly checked, yet no chimpanzee solved the task independently.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:27:27.924Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Bodily Fitness",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A biological state influenced by selective forces, linked to survival and reproduction, which can be affected by the percolating effects of social learning and cultural transmission.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:27:28.048Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Survival",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A key biological outcome driven by selective forces, potentially enhanced by the efficient acquisition of skills through social learning rather than individual innovation.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:27:28.176Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Reproduction",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A key biological outcome driven by selective forces, potentially enhanced by the fitness benefits derived from social learning and cultural traditions.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:27:28.305Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Selective Forces",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Evolutionary pressures that drive the emergence of specific capacities, such as know-how copying or Cumulative Cultural Evolution, which may differ in their primary drivers.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:27:28.438Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Chimpanzee Demonstrators",
        "type": "Person",
        "description": "Specific adult female chimpanzees of middle/high rank selected from each group to be trained as models for social learning experiments.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:28:29.611Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Chimfunshi Research Advisory Board",
        "type": "Organization",
        "description": "Institutional body providing guidelines for the ethical treatment of research subjects, referenced by protocol number 2016C027.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:28:29.755Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Zambia Wildlife Authority",
        "type": "Organization",
        "description": "National authority in Zambia stipulating standards for the treatment of animals, which the research complied with.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:28:29.878Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Weatherall Report",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "International standard for the use of non-human primates in research, cited as a compliance benchmark for the study.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:28:30.003Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Indoor Holding Facility",
        "type": "Location",
        "description": "Specific location within the sanctuary where selected chimpanzee demonstrators were kept isolated during training sessions to prevent premature social transmission.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:28:30.153Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Training Protocol",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The specific method used to train demonstrator chimpanzees, involving 20-minute sessions over eight consecutive days where they explored the apparatus and received human cues.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:28:30.385Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Human Cues",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Assistance provided by researchers during training, such as pushing out the drawer or operating it from outside the room, to help demonstrator chimpanzees understand the apparatus mechanics.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:28:30.509Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Social Learning Phase",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The experimental phase initiated at t331 where trained demonstrator chimpanzees were reintroduced to their groups to facilitate skill acquisition in naive individuals.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:28:30.636Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Miombo Enclosures",
        "type": "Location",
        "description": "Large, forested enclosures at Chimfunshi Wildlife Orphanage Trust where chimpanzees reside, stay outside overnight, and interact with the puzzle box apparatus.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:29:18.872Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Supplemental Feeding",
        "type": "Event",
        "description": "Daily scheduled feeding event occurring between 11:30 and 13:30, during which chimpanzees come indoors from their Miombo enclosures.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:29:19.942Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Food Reward Mechanism",
        "type": "Tool",
        "description": "The internal mechanism of the puzzle box triggered by inserting a wooden ball into the drawer hole, which dispenses a food reward.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:29:25.362Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Chimpanzee Residents",
        "type": "Person",
        "description": "The population of 66 chimpanzees living at Chimfunshi Wildlife Orphanage Trust, of which 61 participated in the social learning phase.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:29:29.525Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Social Learning Phase Participation",
        "type": "Event",
        "description": "The period during which 61 chimpanzees acted as observers or active operators of the puzzle box apparatus to acquire the skill socially.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:29:29.661Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Chimpfunshi Wildlife Orphanage Trust",
        "type": "Organization",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:29:32.815Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Spring Mechanism",
        "type": "Tool",
        "description": "A component of the puzzle box apparatus that secures the drawer, making the action of pulling it out effortful for the chimpanzees.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:03.513Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Peanuts",
        "type": "Tool",
        "description": "The specific food reward (five to eight peeled units) dispensed by the puzzle box upon successful insertion of a wooden ball.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:03.662Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Rank Assessment",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The method used to determine chimpanzee social rank by averaging ordinal rank assessments provided independently by three experienced caretakers.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:03.788Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Unconstrained Model",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A statistical model used in the study to independently estimate the effects of Individual-Level Variables (ILVs) on both asocial and social learning processes.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:03.916Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Multi-model Inference Approach",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "An analytical strategy using Akaike’s Information Criterion (AICc) to evaluate support for different statistical models based on various observation networks.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:04.050Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Akaike’s Information Criterion",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A metric used for model selection, corrected for sample size (AICc), to determine the best fit among competing statistical models in the study.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:04.198Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Individuals Observed Network",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A specific social network structure analyzed to track which individuals were observed by others during the experiment.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:14.507Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Single Observation Network",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A specific social network structure analyzed to model social transmission based on single observation events.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:14.644Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Group Network",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A specific social network structure analyzed to model social transmission at the group level.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:14.776Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Individual-Level Variables",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Variables specific to individual chimpanzees (such as rank) whose effects on asocial and social learning were estimated using the unconstrained model.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:30:19.502Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Hypothesis 1",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Statistical hypothesis positing that social transmission occurs with different strengths in each chimpanzee group (s1 ≠ s2).",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:23.729Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Hypothesis 2",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Statistical hypothesis positing that social transmission occurs with equal strength across all chimpanzee groups (s1 = s2).",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:23.872Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Hypothesis 3",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Statistical hypothesis positing that social transmission occurs only in Group 1, with no transmission in Group 2 (s2 = 0).",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:23.995Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Hypothesis 4",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Statistical hypothesis positing that social transmission occurs only in Group 2, with no transmission in Group 1 (s1 = 0).",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:24.116Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Hypothesis 5",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Statistical hypothesis representing an asocial-learning-only model, where gamma parameters have no effect and are excluded from the model.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:24.245Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Two-hour Test Sessions",
        "type": "Event",
        "description": "Experimental observation periods lasting two hours, during which 39 sessions were conducted per group over a two-month period to collect behavioral data.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:24.367Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Successful Operation",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A coded behavioral event where a chimpanzee successfully inserts a ball into the drawer, causing it to fall audibly into the apparatus, thereby reinstating the drawer.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:24.490Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Attempted Operation",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A coded behavioral event where a chimpanzee interacts with the apparatus (e.g., fiddling with the drawer, bouncing balls) but fails to achieve a successful operation.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:24.613Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Observation Coding",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The method of recording data where an individual is coded as observing if they reside within 1.5 meters of a chimpanzee successfully operating the apparatus.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:24.736Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Eye-level Meshwork Window",
        "type": "Location",
        "description": "A designated space in the outdoor enclosures where successful operations occurred, facilitating straightforward coding of observations due to its specific positioning.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:24.858Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Total Akaike Weight",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A statistical measure used to calculate the total support for hypotheses 1–4 across different observation networks, derived from Akaike’s Information Criterion.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:31:24.981Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Multistate NBDA",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "An extension of Network-based Diffusion Analysis that models transitions between multiple behavioral states (naive, interacting, informed) to elucidate the specific role of social learning in different phases of skill acquisition.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:32:31.897Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Interacting State",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A behavioral state in the multistate model where a chimpanzee has started manipulating the puzzle box task but has not yet successfully solved it.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:32:37.200Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Informed State",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A behavioral state in the multistate model where a chimpanzee has successfully solved the puzzle box task at least once.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:32:37.335Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Order-of-acquisition NBDA",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A variant of Network-based Diffusion Analysis that uses only the sequence order in which individuals acquire a behavior, ignoring the specific timing of acquisition events.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:32:37.466Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Coder Agreement",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "The level of inter-rater reliability among coders, measured at 91.9% for identifying solvers and 85.0% for identifying observers, ensuring data validity.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:32:37.599Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Static Group Network",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A social network model used as a baseline or alternative structure in the analysis, representing fixed group membership rather than dynamic observation patterns.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:33:52.354Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Maternal Kin Bias",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A hypothesized social learning pattern where chimpanzees are more likely to observe and learn from maternal relatives compared to non-kin individuals.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:33:56.310Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Age-based Observation Bias",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A hypothesized pattern in social learning where chimpanzees show a preference for observing either older or younger individuals within the group.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:33:56.446Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Rank-based Observation Bias",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A hypothesized pattern in social learning where chimpanzees preferentially observe individuals of higher or lower social rank.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:33:56.580Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Generalized Linear Mixed Model",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A statistical model with a logit link function used to test for patterns in the observation network, accounting for random effects such as individual propensity to observe or be observed.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:33:56.708Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Observer Propensity",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A random effect variable in the statistical model representing the individual variation in a chimpanzee's tendency to observe others.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:33:56.840Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Manipulator Propensity",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A random effect variable in the statistical model representing the individual variation in a chimpanzee's tendency to be observed while manipulating the task.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:33:56.988Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Bayesian Inference",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A statistical method used in the study to obtain posterior samples for model parameters, allowing for the estimation of odds ratios and their uncertainty.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:34:42.184Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Markov Chain Monte Carlo",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A computational algorithm used within Bayesian inference to sample from probability distributions and estimate model parameters.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:34:47.764Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "JAGS",
        "type": "Tool",
        "description": "Just Another Gibbs Sampler, a program for analysis of Bayesian hierarchical models using Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) simulation, run via the R statistical environment.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:34:47.909Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "runjags",
        "type": "Tool",
        "description": "An R package, version 2.0.4, used to interface with JAGS for running Bayesian models within the R statistical environment.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:34:48.041Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "Odds Ratios",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "Statistical measures estimated in the study to quantify the effect size of social learning and other variables, calculated as the back-transformed mean of the posterior distribution.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:34:48.182Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
      {
        "name": "95% Highest Posterior Density Intervals",
        "type": "Concept",
        "description": "A Bayesian credible interval used to express the uncertainty around the estimated odds ratios, containing 95% of the posterior distribution.",
        "tags": [],
        "created": "2026-05-25T00:34:48.322Z",
        "source": "chimpanzee-social-skill-acquisition-leeuwen-2024.pdf"
      },
