      {
        "content": "In Group 1, several chimpanzees including BJ (205 observations), Gonzaga (99 observations), and Irene (153 observations) failed to acquire the skill despite extensive observational exposure. Renate, who had the highest number of observations in the group at 406, also did not acquire the skill, indicating that high exposure alone does not guarantee mastery. This suggests that factors beyond mere quantity of observation, such as attention quality or cognitive interpretation, play a critical role in social learning outcomes.",
        "title": "High-observation non-learners in Group 1",
