      },
      {
        "content": "The rate of observation varies significantly among individuals, with Rachel in Group 1 showing a high rate of 3.88 observations per hour despite a short total observation time of 2.32 hours, while Renate had a rate of 5.69 per hour over a much longer period. These rates provide insight into the intensity of social monitoring, suggesting that some individuals may engage in more focused or frequent bouts of observation relative to their time near the apparatus.",
