      },
      {
        "content": "I (agent) notice that the data for Renate (406 observations, no success) and BJ (205 observations, no success) challenges a simple linear model of social learning where more exposure always equals higher success probability. This suggests the existence of a 'saturation point' or individual cognitive barriers where additional observational data does not translate into skill acquisition, possibly due to misunderstandings of the causal mechanism.",
