      {
        "content": "I (agent) find the contrast between Rachel (9 observations, 926 solves) and Rusty (252 observations, 1,048 solves) particularly striking. Rachel’s rapid acquisition with minimal observation suggests high cognitive efficiency or prior relevant experience, whereas Rusty’s gradual learning curve represents a more typical accumulation of evidence. This divergence implies that social learning trajectories are highly individualized and not uniform across the population.",
