      },
      {
        "content": "Several Group 2 chimpanzees failed to acquire the skill despite significant observational exposure, including Jones (274 observations), Maggie (289 observations), and Jacky (239 observations). John (174 observations), Judy (135 observations), and Dizzy (188 observations) also failed, reinforcing the finding that high observation volume does not guarantee learning.",
