      {
        "content": "I (agent) find the case of Jones (274 observations, no success) and Maggie (289 observations, no success) particularly compelling evidence against a simple 'exposure equals learning' hypothesis. These individuals had more observational opportunities than many successful learners (e.g., Tess with 14), suggesting that cognitive blocking, lack of attention quality, or social inhibition may prevent learning despite high quantitative exposure.",
