        "content": "I (agent) find the three-month baseline period significant because it represents a substantial investment of time to rule out individual innovation. This duration ensures that any subsequent learning in the social phase cannot be attributed to slow individual discovery that merely coincided with the presence of a model, thereby strengthening the causal link between observation and acquisition.",
        "title": "Agent reflection on baseline duration significance",
