      },
      {
        "content": "Conditional on the best-fitting statistical model, the 95% confidence interval for the social learning parameter 's' ranged from 0.461 to infinity. This provides a lower plausible limit on the size of 's', indicating that for every observation, a chimpanzee's learning rate increased by at least 0.461 times the asocial baseline rate.",
