      {
        "content": "The baseline rate for asocial learning was specifically calibrated to a female chimpanzee of middle rank and average age. Using this demographic as the reference point standardizes the comparison, allowing the social learning effect to be quantified relative a specific, controlled asocial baseline rather than a generalized average.",
