      {
        "content": "The study subjects were semi-wild chimpanzees housed at the Chimfunshi Wildlife Orphanage Trust in Zambia. The sample was specifically composed of two distinct groups: chimpanzees who had been rescued from detrimental conditions and those who were born directly within the sanctuary. This mixed background provides a unique demographic context for observing social learning in a semi-captive environment.",
